flac2alac is a shell script to convert FLAC (Free Lossless Audio Codec) files to ALAC (Apple Lossless Audio Codec) format, used on iPod/iPhone/iPad.

Author Viktor Minko

based on:
flac2alac by Arlindo "Nighto" Pereira
First posted on http://nighto.net/convertendo-flac-para-alac/
(C) 2010
Licensed on GPLv3

Features:

Split on tracks using cue sheet
Folders processing (inc. recursive)
Deleting files after converson

Dependencies:

flac
ffmpeg
cuebreakpoints
shnsplit
cuetag


Usage exampl:

flac2alac flacFolder -r -d
